    {
      "$type": "Models.Memo, Models",
      "Text": "# CLEM herd management examples\n\nThe following simulations provide an example of each of the tasks performed in the RuminantActivityManage activity. You can use these examples to explore the model and check that the model is working as expected.\n\nEach example will build on the previous example until a managed herd is provided. For example we need to include the growing out (or at least sales) of young males to maintain the herd size, so this example is included in the breeder management example.\n\n## Help\nThe CLEM help system provides a model overview, user guide (how to) and a full description of every CLEM component, as well as in depth discussions on modelling various farm systems and what components to use. The Help documentation can be accessed by clicking the Help button beside the component name in the right hand information pane after selecting any CLEM component from your simulation tree or at [CLEM Help online](http://www.apsim.info/CLEM/Content/Home.htm).",
      "Name": "Details",
      "ResourceName": null,
      "Children": [],
      "Enabled": true,
      "ReadOnly": false
    },
    {
      "$type": "Models.Core.Simulation, Models",
      "Name": "Increase herd at start",
      "ResourceName": null,
      "Children": [
        {
          "$type": "Models.Memo, Models",
          "Text": "Herd management example\n# Increase male and female breeders at start of simulation\n\n## Activity\nActivities.Manage herd.Manage numbers (Ruminant activity manage)\n\n## Properties\nin Properties tab - Statup category\n- adjust female breeding numbers at start up = True\n- adjust male breeding numbers at start up = True\n\nin Properties tab - Herd size category\n- maximum number of breeders = 40\n- maximum sires kept = 0.1 (10% of max breeders)\n\n## Initial herd\n- 20 female breeders and 2 male breeders\n- 5 Females age 24 months\n- 10 Females age 36 months\n- 5 Females age 48 months\n- 2 Males age 42 and sires\n\n## Results\n- See category FillInitialHerd entries in HerdLedger report\n- See herd size in first month in HerdSummary report",
          "Name": "Description",
          "ResourceName": null,
          "Children": [],
          "Enabled": true,
          "ReadOnly": false
        },
