    {
      "$type": "Models.Core.Simulation, Models",
      "Name": "Grow out males",
      "ResourceName": null,
      "Children": [
        {
          "$type": "Models.Memo, Models",
          "Text": "Herd management example\n# Manage males as grow out with age/weight sales\n\n## Activity\nActivities.Manage herd.Manage numbers (Ruminant activity manage)\n\n## Properties\n\nin Properties tab - Herd size category\n- Perform growing out of young males = true\n- Sell grow out males = true\n- Grow out males selling age = 18\n- Grow out male selling weight = 350\n- Castrate males = true\n\nOther settings\n- maximum breeder herd to 60 allowing increase from initial herd of 20\n- minimum breeder herd to 20 so no purchases will be made until herd falls below 20\n\n## Initial herd\n- 20 female breeders and 2 male breeders\n- 5 Females age 24 months\n- 10 Females age 36 months\n- 5 Females age 48 months\n- 2 Males age 42 and sires\n\n## Results\n- See herd AgeWeightSales category in HerdLedger report where individuals are of class = Castrated\n- See herd size in year one in HerdSummary report to see juvenile males castrated\n- The first castrated males from weaning and herd management appear in January 1972\n- The first age/weight sales of grow out males occur during herd management in August 1972",
          "Name": "Description",
          "ResourceName": null,
          "Children": [],
          "Enabled": true,
          "ReadOnly": false
        },
        {
          "$type": "Models.Clock, Models",
          "Start": "1970-01-01T00:00:00",
