    {
      "$type": "Models.Core.Simulation, Models",
      "Name": "Grow out females",
      "ResourceName": null,
      "Children": [
        {
          "$type": "Models.Memo, Models",
          "Text": "Herd management example\n# Grow out and sell for age/weight any excess young females\n\n## Activity\nActivities.Manage herd.Manage numbers (Ruminant activity manage)\n\n## Properties\n\n- Perform growing out of young males as per previous example\n- Breeder herd management as per last example\n- Perform growing out of young females = true\n- Sell grow out females = true\n- Grow out females selling age = 24\n- Grow out female selling weight = 300\n* Note difference in age and weight criteria between males and females.\n\n## Initial herd\n- 20 female breeders and 2 male breeders\n\n## Results\n- The HerdLedger report (filter for rows with [#Class] = 'PreBreeder')\n- The PreBreeder entries appear from Aug 1972 when a prebreeder dies\n- In August 1976 the first group of female prebreeders in the growout herd are sold for age/weight sales.\n- The Herdsummary shows number in each class each month (plotted for prebreeders in PreBreeders graph)\n\n### Number of breeders graph\n- The number of female PreBreeders fluctuates after 1972 based on individuals being sold when they reach age or weight, deaths and when returned to the herd to replace breeders as required.\n",
          "Name": "Description",
          "ResourceName": null,
          "Children": [],
          "Enabled": true,
          "ReadOnly": false
        },
